article.linkText: Reynolds scores 27 in Green Bay's 78-61 win against Robert Morris
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. -- — Noah Reynolds scored 27 points as Green Bay beat Robert Morris 78-61 on Sunday. Reynolds shot 10 for 17 (3 for 7 from 3-point range) and 4 of 4 from the free throw line for the Phoenix (8-7, 3-1 Horizon League). Foster Wonders scored 13 points while going 4 of 9 from the floor, including 3 for 7 from 3-point range, and 2 for 3 from the line. Elijah Jones shot 5 of 7 from the field and 2 for 3 from the line to finish with 12 points, while adding six rebounds. TJ Wainwright finished with 18 points for the Colonials (4-11, 0-4). Stephaun Walker added 14 points for Robert Morris. NEXT UP Both teams next play Thursday. Green Bay visits Detroit Mercy and Robert Morris squares off against IUPUI at home. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
